Hello again

...we have a small favour to ask. More people are reading and supporting The Guardian’s independent, investigative journalism than ever before. We’ve chosen a different approach – all of our reporting remains open and accessible to everyone, funded by reader support.

The Guardian will engage with the most critical issues of our time – from the escalating climate catastrophe to widespread inequality to the influence of big tech on our lives. At a time when factual information is a necessity, we believe that each of us deserves access to accurate reporting with integrity at its heart.

Our editorial independence means we set our own agenda, free from commercial and political bias. This means we can give a voice to those less heard, explore where others turn away, and rigorously challenge those in power. We need your support to keep delivering quality journalism and to protect our editorial independence.

Whichever way you choose to support us, it’s so valuable for our future.
